criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Pathologically diagnosed middle and lower thoracic IA-IIIB esophageal cancer after
             surgeries;

          -  Patients who received minimally invasive radical dissections of Ivor-Lewis and
             Mckeown;

          -  Patients who received tubular gastroesophageal reconstruction;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients complicated with arrhythmia, or serious disfunctions of heart, lung, liver,
             and kidney before surgeries;

          -  Patients with second primary tumors;

          -  Patients who received abdominal or thoracic surgeries;

          -  Patients who received gastrostomy or nesteostomy before surgeries;

          -  Patients with suspected cervical lymph metastases (in the subgroup of the patients who
             received the surgery of Mckeown)
